<poem>
    <coder>TL</coder>
<header>
<title>To America</title>
<byLine poet="Johnson_JW">James Weldon Johnson</byLine>
</header>
<content>
<line n="1" stanza="1">How would you have us<punc type="comma">,</punc> as we are?</line>
<line n="2" stanza="1">Or sinking <punc type="open_parenthesis">'</punc>neath the load we bear<punc type="question_mark">?</punc></line>
<line n="3" stanza="1">Our eyes fixed forward on a star<punc type="question_mark">?</punc></line>
<line n="4" stanza="1">Or gazing empty at despair<punc type="question_mark">?</punc></line>

<line n="5" stanza="2">Rising or falling<punc type="question_mark">?</punc> Men or things?</line>
<line n="6" stanza="2">With dragging pace or footsteps fleet<punc type="question_mark">?</punc></line>
<line n="7" stanza="2">Strong<punc type="comma">,</punc> willing sinews in your wings<punc type="question_mark">?</punc></line>
<line n="8" stanza="2">Or tightening chains about your feet<punc type="question_mark">?</punc></line>
    </content>
</poem>